- New TestRunShowFullProducer: capture a stage with --harness claude-code --harness-version 2.1.150 --model claude-opus-4-7 --skill-id dev-planner --skill-repo codewithjv-agent-skills --skill-version v3, then run show and assert all three appear: `harness:     claude-code 2.1.150`, `model:       claude-opus-4-7`, `skill:       dev-planner@v3 (codewithjv-agent-skills)`.
- Edge: optionally a partial-producer case (harness set, model empty) asserting harness line present but no `model:` line — covers independent conditional omission.

**Docs:** docs/run.md WILL drift (note for Docs phase, do not edit in Plan): the example block (lines 54-62) shows the old `skill id/repo/ver` lines and must show `harness:`/`model:`/`skill:`; the per-stage field list (lines 69-70) lists `skill id`, `skill repo`, `skill ver` and must describe `harness` (optional), `model` (optional), and consolidated `skill: id@version (repo)`, noting harness/model are omitted when empty for legacy manifests.

**Risks:** None significant. Pure output-format change in one function. Producer.Skill guaranteed populated by decode so no nil/empty-skill crash. Only coupling risk is the literal-string test assertions and the shipped doc, both explicitly in scope.

**Tier:** Tier 1 — user-facing product output AND a shipped-doc change (docs/run.md). This is a CLI bead: Verify requires a built-binary manual test (build etude, capture a full-producer stage and a legacy stage into a run, run `etude run show` against each, confirm full shows harness/model/skill@version and legacy shows skill only with no empty harness/model lines).

